{"id":819820954,"question_id":653,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 year, 8 months","timestamp":1665458006,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"9 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/819820954/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Two Sum IV - Input is a BST","memory":"53.4 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\n * public class TreeNode {\n *     int val;\n *     TreeNode left;\n *     TreeNode right;\n *     TreeNode() {}\n *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\n *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {\n *         this.val = val;\n *         this.left = left;\n *         this.right = right;\n *     }\n * }\n */\nclass Solution {\n    \n    HashSet<Integer> set = new HashSet<>();\n    \n    \n    public boolean findTarget(TreeNode root, int k) {\n    \n        if(root==null)\n            return false;\n        \n        if(set.contains(root.val))\n            return true;\n        else\n            set.add(k-root.val);\n        \n        \n        return findTarget(root.right, k) || findTarget(root.left, k);\n        \n        \n    }\n    \n    \n    \n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"two-sum-iv-input-is-a-bst","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
